The paper discusses Multi-Agent Reinforcement Learning (MARL) and its application in multi-task environments. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also focuses on coordination, efficiency/fairness, and common-pool resource sharing, which are topics related to Multi-Agent Systems (MAS), making cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) the second likely category. The paper also discusses value-based and policy-based methods, which are topics related to Machine Learning (ML), making cs.LG (Machine Learning) the third likely category. The paper also discusses the convergence of the algorithms, which is a topic related to Robotics (RO), making cs.RO (Robotics) the fourth likely category. Finally, the paper discusses the exploration of the agents, which is a topic related to Systems and Control (SY), making cs.SY (Systems and Control) the fifth likely category.
